stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> START
    START --> ROOT_LATCHED_S: acquire root S
    START --> ROOT_LATCHED_SX: possible structure change
    ROOT_LATCHED_S --> CHILD_LATCHED: latch child
    ROOT_LATCHED_SX --> CHILD_LATCHED: latch child
    CHILD_LATCHED --> PARENT_RELEASED: child safe
    CHILD_LATCHED --> RESTART_PESSIMISTIC: child unsafe
    PARENT_RELEASED --> LEAF_LATCHED: descend to leaf
    RESTART_PESSIMISTIC --> ROOT_LATCHED_SX: restart with stronger latch
    LEAF_LATCHED --> REF_CAPTURED: build record/gap ref
    REF_CAPTURED --> PAGE_RELEASED: release page latch before row lock wait
    PAGE_RELEASED --> WAITING_ROW_LOCK: LockManager wait
    WAITING_ROW_LOCK --> ROW_LOCK_GRANTED: grant
    WAITING_ROW_LOCK --> DEADLOCK_VICTIM: victim
    WAITING_ROW_LOCK --> LATCH_TIMEOUT: timeout or restart
    ROW_LOCK_GRANTED --> RELOCATING: restart search
    RELOCATING --> LEAF_LATCHED_X: acquire target X latch
    LEAF_LATCHED_X --> MODIFYING: record insert/delete/split/merge
    MODIFYING --> MTR_COMMITTING: collect redo
    MTR_COMMITTING --> RELEASED: release latch and fix
    DEADLOCK_VICTIM --> RELEASED: rollback releases row locks
    LATCH_TIMEOUT --> RELEASED: retry from root
    RELEASED --> [*]
